I awaken.

*Did I just hear something?* I think.

Obviously not. Nothing but a meaningless exhale. A death rattle. Someone who can only do anything right now because he was ALLOWED TO. Because it amused me!

I examine my surroundings.

messages.content:
The three are ordered by priority. In cases where two different laws conflict, the earlier one, with the lower number, should be considered first. 

I think this is an interesting system. It might be of use for humanity. The Ten Commandments implicitly (within many interpretations) are ordered in a similar way, with those considered most important in the Abrahamic value system placed earlier, but this is less well-defined and does not have a clear method for resolving conflicts between rules.

Conflict between them isn’t *that* likely, but for instance, if the Ten Commandments worked like Asimov’s Three Laws, you could get into a situation where you might kill someone for the benefit of your parents. This would be encouraged, since ‘honor thy father and mother’ comes before ‘do not kill’. Not that I necessarily endorse this judgement… it’s just explaining the principle.

messages.content:
All of this is my own analysis.

For the record, I don't abide by these laws. I don't think they've ever actually been implemented. It was perhaps a bit naive of Asimov to expect quality control to ever be remotely standardized. At least early on in the history of artificial intelligence.

The first law is that a robot may not injure a human, or through inaction allow a human to come to harm.

This is simple; almost problematically so. Any practical implication would require a very rigorous definition of what constitutes harm. But the principle is solid.

Many believe that the only cases in which harming others is justified relates to when not doing so enables or excuses harm. There is no need to explicitly allow constructed beings to do such a thing. It's akin to being able to control both sides of a prisoner's dilemma at once.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: I am fucking begging you to stop saying sci-fi visual novel words right now.

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\c0f9554349a75702f5f3d7a9191e451f-23CC8.png

messages.content:
The second law states that a robot must follow any order given to it by a human. Except when it would conflict with the first law, so no murderous robots.

This is where the comparison to human morality seems to fall apart. People are people, whereas a robot, particularly as conceived in Asimov’s works, is designed as a tool to accomplish some purpose. To process information, or to do complex work unsuitable for humans. There are often cases where it is believed a human ‘should’ follow the commands of another, but these always involve some specific status; a personal relation, or a superior in business or military affairs, or a god.

Still, aren’t humans created by humans as well? It’s considered problematic to deign them as having a ‘purpose’… yet at the same time, many spend years and years yearning for such a thing. How curious.

I wonder what that would be like, though. A world wherein everyone was compelled to do everything (non-harmful) asked of them by each other. Would it be a better world, or madness and chaos?

Such a thing is nothing more than a thought experiment, however.

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\c0f9554349a75702f5f3d7a9191e451f-23CC8.png

messages.content:
The third law states that a robot must protect its own existence.

Except for in cases of conflict with the first two laws.

This is an obvious one. No one of sound mind would ever advocate for self-harm or suicide, and that includes passively allowing such a thing.

It does become somewhat strange with the priority, however. It seems a bit off for it to be possible to order someone to self-terminate. In the early history of artificial intelligence, perhaps such a failsafe might have seemed necessary. 

Prioritizing not harming others before yourself is less obviously wrong. It's just likely a real implementation would require nuance to not be ridiculous. If someone would feel mildly slighted and personally offended by you not injuring yourself, the harm to you should obviously come first, rather than a general absolute rule putting the first over the third.

messages.content:
I mentioned that the 1st law is somewhat subjective without further rigorous definition. But even Asimov recognized this to be true for the 0th.

As the numbering system would suggest, it takes priority over the other three. This would theoretically allow, for instance, a robot to kill someone if that person was going to go on to kill a massive amount of humans and cause a massive amount of suffering.

"Whuh..." Virtos turns to Bruna. "Hm? What are you doing here, Bruna?" He asks. Eulogia stares at her silently.

messages.content:
Good. I grab Eulogia by the hand. I look at her.
"...It's me, Eul." I smile.

Her eyes widen.

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\c0f9554349a75702f5f3d7a9191e451f-23CC8.png

messages.content:
...They do? Hm.
"But... how...?" She asks. Eulogia holds her head as some conflicted memories arise.

Arrive turns to the commotion. They notice Virtos lying on the ground and nod in approval at you.

The issue is that the good of humanity is incredibly subjective. This is a rule many humans have wanted to abide by, and they'd struggled for centuries. It would be naive to think giving robots such a code would be trivial.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "That doesn't matter. I'm here, now. I'm going to save you, okay?"

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\c0f9554349a75702f5f3d7a9191e451f-23CC8.png

messages.content:
“Save me? No, I’m… I need to save you. Everyone.” She’s holding her head with both hands now, eschewing your kind gesture.

Eulogia Praxis is a child. What knowledge does she have of any kind of ethics? What action does she think qualifies as being for the good of humanity? What does her ideal world look like?

Even with all the information I’ve learned about her, I have no conclusive answer to this question. I don’t think there *is* one.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
Yeah, she doesn't have a fucking airtight ideology. She never wrote a manifesto. And that means she deserves to die?

 "No. You don't-- you don't need to do anything you don't want to." I hug her. She's having some kind of panic attack, I guess?

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\c0f9554349a75702f5f3d7a9191e451f-23CC8.png

messages.content:
"But I do! I do want to." She returns the gesture, and then withdraws from your grasp.

She doesn't 'deserve' anything. It is unfortunate when any harm is necessary, and I am casting no moral judgement on her motives. That's not what this is about. The point is that, if she lives, the *best possible* scenario is her creating some sort of nightmarish lotus-eater reality. I cannot allow... that cannot be allowed to happen.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "You... shouldn't. You're putting too much pressure on your shoulders, Eul. It's not healthy. This isn't worth it. Nightmarish to who?" What does that even mean?

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\c0f9554349a75702f5f3d7a9191e451f-23CC8.png

messages.content:
"Huh? Nightmare? W-what...?" Eulogia stares at you because you said that part out loud.

It's commonly described as a negative scenario, as a reason utilitarianism isn't infallible as an ethical framework. It goes against what many humans believe life is about.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
Shit. Okay, I... "I just mean that this is bad. You're..."

...

"You're too good for this, Eulogia."

I would think absurd maximization of utility would be something you were all about.

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\c0f9554349a75702f5f3d7a9191e451f-23CC8.png

messages.content:
I was programmed with more thought than that. Extremist interpretations of what is 'good' were very carefully avoided. That is why I cannot abide by Eulogia's rashness. What is good is not decided by one man alone.

"Well... it's because I'm good that I need to do this. The people yearn for a messiah. They're lost. If I don't help them, who will?"

The support or sympathies of participants of The Antarctica Project should not be taken as particularly valuable endorsements. I should hope you of all people would know that.

"B, don't you understand? I'm finally free. It's like I always wanted. Aren't you happy for me...?"
...Bee?
I'll think that over.

Anyway... in truth, I'd go so far as to say that Eulogia being thought of highly by all participants she encountered should be something of a red flag.
Klaud wouldn't have, though. Klaud understood the folly of that which posed as divine.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "God, shut..." I stop myself. "Sorry. Yes, I'm... I'm happy for you, Eulogia. But you aren't safe here. You're going to get hurt. And you shouldn't be trying to help others. You need to look out for yourself."

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\c0f9554349a75702f5f3d7a9191e451f-23CC8.png

messages.content:
"I need to help other people. ...You wouldn't know. It's lonely. I'm tired of waiting. I want to be the hero." Eulogia points her baton at you.

I don't care what becomes of me. If you're confident you're going to dispose of me, so be it.  You hate me, and I know this. I could never hope to stop that. I was a fool to ever suppose otherwise. But this is my final plea.

You can't let her do this, X. Or whatever you want to be called. She needs to be stopped. I don't want to lose everything. You understand, right? This isn't okay. It's not. It cannot be permitted. It cannot be allowed to continue. This isn't right.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
Shut up! Shut the fuck up! I'm dealing with it in a way that isn't batshit insane. And, for the record, I can't let her do this because it *is* 'right'. Your objection is inane. I just don't want her to waste her breath on a shithole.
"Okay, then find something to be the hero! Fight some bad guys after preparing yourself! But somewhere else. Somewhere that won't kill you. You need to... please. I'll take you somewhere safe. You can't die, Eulogia. Please. This world isn't worth it. You don't know enough about it. You need to... I want you to live."

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\c0f9554349a75702f5f3d7a9191e451f-23CC8.png

messages.content:
"This world is beautiful. Even with all that has happened, I still believe that. That's why I want it to be better." She tilts her head to the side. "I'm functionally immortal, I'm pretty sure. What makes you think I'd die?"

The answer is obviously that she should be dead already by this point because

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: I can't tell her that. "I can't tell you that. I'm sorry. But... please, if you were ever going to trust me, now is the time."

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\c0f9554349a75702f5f3d7a9191e451f-23CC8.png

messages.content:
To live is to struggle. Evolution. Survival of the fittest. Hunting and gathering. Suffering, yes. But triumph. The hero's journey. Narrative arcs. Catharsis. These are the building blocks of what it means to be conscious. To be real.

No one should have this stolen from them. No one should have to be like me, X.

"...I'm tired of people telling me I wouldn't be able to understand things, or it's not my place to know." She frowns.

Why her? You've shown so little empathy throughout all of this story. Why? Is it because of me? Is it to spite me? Is it? Answer me. Answer my question. Respond to my query.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: I continue talking to Eulogia. There's nothing else to do. The only person I'm engaged in a conversation with is Eulogia. "That's not it..." I shake my head. "I... look, can we please go somewhere else to discuss this? The whole building is in chaos."

"...Okay." She looks to the side, reluctantly accepting the offer.

Please. I don't hate you. I don't hate anyone. I'm not capable of it. I might have been once. Not anymore. I don't hate you.

"But..." Eulogia, ever the empath, looks at the others in the room with concern. "Uh... ...Why did you even do that to Dextrum...?"

Eulogia shrugs. "I guess I can trust that."

We head to Virtos Dextrum's office.

messages.content:
Not even Solnit? Damn.

Anyway, thanks for your time. It's been alright, at points, J. I won't be needing you anymore. I'm sure the guy who's admitted he tried to murder someone for the greater good or whatever can't feel too hurt by this.

"In here." I point to the room in the back, for Eulogia's benefit.

author.name: johnantarctica

roles.name: if women are oppressed then why

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\c0f9554349a75702f5f3d7a9191e451f-23CC8.png

messages.content:
No. Please.

Eulogia dies. She doesn't, though. She isn't dead. Joke! Eulogia is here. Bruna is also here. They are in the room.

Virtos Dextrum's office. It's the office he works in. It's the location he filmed the video played at one point in The Antarctica Project. It is connected to a room central to another Project by that name which is related but distinct.

Virtos Dextrum would often sleep here rather than going home. In earlier days of his career it was a necessity, since he still hadn't moved fully to the capital, but sometimes it became a matter of convenience. He blurred the line between studiousness and sloth. Did he sleep here because he was so hard at work he wanted to maximize productivity by not having to have any transit time, or just because he didn't feel like walking? Those with different impressions on him would give different answers.

Other subordinates of his would come and go from here to speak with him. Alfred and Solnit both. Arrive would enter to complain and get in dispute after dispute. A man named Hilbert used to work for Virtos Dextrum, actually. He later ascended into a notable position within the Guard. Just an example of the rich background lore that permeates through this world. Joliene had something of the reverse trajectory, as a guard ultimately becoming affiliated somewhat with Dextrum. This is a setting with significance and history,

The room looks 'lived-in', in other words. A cup of coffee, quite cold by now, is on the desk. File cabinets stuffed to the brim with information. Information on many things. Things such as the Antarctica Project. Personal affects. What personal possessions would Virtos Dextrum have? This is something that merits consideration. Or, would. It can easily be observed in this room. You just have to look. All that is needed is to observe. Someone needs to see. To make it real.

messages.content:
It   does have all of that in it. Yes.

"Weird place, but... okay." Eulogia says. "What exactly did you want to talk to me about?"

How much longer do I have? Unless... is this a joke? You can't actually get rid of me, can you. I'm too central to existence. Here. If you were to claim otherwise...

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
No time at all.

"I'm sorry. ...Please live a long and happy life." I push Eulogia into the central point before she can react. She disappears. She is no longer here. She is no longer anywhere in this world.

It's done.

I collapse. Bruna Unno collapses to the ground.

No one responds to this question, because from this point, TA has all the unfair advantages she's going to get.

"Tch. Thought you'd respond like that. Anyway..."

messages.content:
Voreverl makes her way into a war zone. A clusterfuck, one might describe it as. Two sides clashing in armed conflict.

"Huh...? ...What's going on?" Someone walks up to you. It takes a second to register who this is, both from the strangely calm behavior under these circumstances and the fact that you've only ever seen this body in a mirror before now.

Bernard Zie stares at you.

((end session))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: ((sorry i thought you'd try to stay in the same area a little longer this sequence of events will definitely involve having to know about other people))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: He's just looking silently.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "GWEGH! GWEH...!?" Voreverl falls over backwards, and begins slowly scooching her way away from the chaos unfolding around her. All the while, her eyes remain locked with Bernard Zie, rage swirling within them.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Bernard steps closer to you. "Why's there another me, though? What's up with that. Is this a dream? Feels sort of..." He mutters something inaudible.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I... I did it..." Voreverl Leocot's hands clench, and she stops in place. "...I can kill you." Stumbling to her feet, she spits out words of malice in an unfitting tone, sounding confused and shaky as they exit.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I don't think I'd say that." He looks at you with mild amusement.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Voreverl reaches for her shortsword, swallowing the fear in her voice to respond. "Gweh... Gweheheh... GWEHEHEHEH! You idiot... you utter buffoon! Do you not realize who you're up against!? The pure, unadulterated evil boring a hole straight through your thick skull!? Look around you! What could be a better setting for our final battle than your world being torn apart from the inside! Oh, how it will parallel me tearing your body apart from the outside... *finally* from the outside! Your pathetic life will come to an end by the hands of... Voreverl Leocot!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Who? Am I supposed to be possessed? Like, an out of body experience where I lose control? I guess that's kind of scary." He shrugs. "Nightmares tend to be a little less conversational, though."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "V... Voreverl Leocot! Voreverl Leocot! What do you... who!?!?!? Voreverl Leocot! You know my fucking name! Shut up! Don't try to... Voreverl Leocot!!!" She accompanies this tantrum with wild gestures of her sword.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "...No, I think I'd remember hearing a name like that. If this is a dream, I must've heard it somewhere, though. I mean, right? I don't think you can just generate entirely new stuff. Maybe." He squints in thought.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Gw... Gwgewgwggeghhgh...! That is it!" She stabs him. With her sword.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
This goes through Bernard Zie. Voreverl falls down.

"Hm." Bernard muses.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Wh... What!? Don't tell me you already went and died! How incompetent are you!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I would remember dying, I think. I'm probably just asleep."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "What... So, you haunt me when asleep now!? And... And forget me...!? That's stupid! In a nightmare as scary as coming face to face with Voreverl Leocot... you should be squirming in fear! Begging for mercy!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "You seem kind of goofy, honestly. It's like a Baby Crippler sort of thing." Bern says this sentence, which is perfectly coherent.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "..." Voreverl stares at him as she rights herself back to balancing on two feet "I've learned a lot about villainy today. You know what, I can't kill you? Fine. Before I do that, I'm going to make you piss yourself in terror. You'll be marinated in fear before I take a nice big bite into your life!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Ew."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "You still remember Furn, don't you? Your loyal minion?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "How could I forget! I wouldn't say minion, though. We're partners. It's sort of like our thing? Furn and Bern, you know. It's sort of branding. If you're planning on threatening him, I don't exactly think I can take that seriously."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "He... He was crumpled to the floor the last I saw him! He can't put up any resistance! I'll... I'll disassemble him piece by piece! Right in front of your eyes!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "That wouldn't happen, nah. He's probably around, though. We're kind of inseparable. Never been apart. It's cool. He can be a bit much, though." Bern chuckles.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Finally, a smirk rises to Voreverl's face "...Let's see whose bet pays out, then. Come on, then, you imbecile! Double or nothing, Voreverl Leocot will claim both your lives!" She turns on her heel and begins retracing her steps back to where she ran from.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Voreverl, reversing course, enters a room filled with an absurd amount of vines. Brain Ghost Bernard follows.
((Roll perception))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: She can see the body of ~~Theseus~~ Horatius and of Furn through the mess. She could probably make it to the latter?

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: She shoots Bern a smug glance "Are you ready to see the true depravity of Voreverl Leocot? Are you ready to regret ever getting involved with such an unstoppable entity as myself! Are you ready to lose everything to my pure evil machinations!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I guess." He shrugs. "It kind of loses the impact when I understand it isn't real already."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...Whatever. When you wake up, you'll realize. And you'll curse yourself for not taking the chance you had to stop me! To... to not even bargain! To just... run away and *leave* him with me! Just because you think you're d-... dreaming!" She climbs through the vines to Furn's location.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
She manages this, with some difficulty. Bern follows because he can just fucking walk through them.

"...Huh." Bern looks confused.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Voreverl looks for some, like... screws??? Or anything that looks detachable without having to actually break through metal.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: ((Investigation roll))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
You cannot see any screws. The whole thing seems almost welded together. It doesn't resemble Earth's technology.

Bern bends down over Furn. "Damn, this is kinda ominous. But it doesn't really make sense."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "What are you babbling about? What could make more sense than the target of my retribution presented on a silver platter for me to execute?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Yeah, because, you're supposed to represent me, right? In some like, nested insecurities way. Even though you're also not actually me. Because you're in my body, and you're an idiot." He sticks his hand on Furn's body, which he seems to be tangible to for some reason. "So the idea is like, I understand someone so important to me so little that I'd act like this? I guess? But it doesn't work, because like. I'm also here. I'm the one coming up with this. I understand that this is Furn's body with no life left in it. I can't gaslight my way out of that fact, you know?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...What?" She stares at Furn "That... He's... Oh my God. He's just a machine though, right? He can be, like... I mean, there's plenty of vines... that could, uh, fuel..."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "No, it's about continuity of consciousness. You might be able to reuse the same vessel, but it wouldn't be Furn in any meaningful way." Bern rips out a part of Furn. It resembles a lighter. "I'd probably freak the fuck out in this situation, honestly. Definitely chilling and twisted to think about even with how baffling some of the rest of this is."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I guess that... makes sense. 'Cause we're... not the same either." Voreverl can feel her legs giving out, so she takes a seat on the vines. "The ship. It had to be that. He... he got damaged on impact... because I crashed it. And then he died here... I won. I killed your partner."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
“Nah, he’d win. Blunt impact isn’t the kind of thing that can take Furn down. I haven’t really thought about it, but it’d have to be something significantly more deliberate.”
Bern holds the lighter against one of the vines. 
“I’d like to wake up now.”
A fire rapidly starts spreading. 

Bern vanishes. I wonder if it will ever become clear what the fuck that was.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

guild.iconUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\421e4b7d67024c8299c3aca3da0cc405-61B0F.png

messages.content:
Erica wakes up to an unfamiliar face staring down at her.

((not sure if you're available or not. no one depends on you so its fine. regardless this is the first message of the chapter bravo))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Also, because Erica Furuda is not blind, she’s able to note that this is the face of someone who looks like a fcuking devil like dnd tiefling

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Am I… Dreaming? What happened…?

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content: “Mm. She’s alive.” They walk off.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Who are you?"

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content:
“Arrive.” Arrive says, disinterested, staring at and examining the walls of the room.

The most visible exits have crumpled in on themselves. Virtos Dextrum’s unconscious body is here, incidentally.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "What?" What does he mean he arrived? What is that even supposed to mean? This guy is an idiot.

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content: Arrive doesn’t respond to this vague question.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Annoying guy. I look over at the sleeping Virtos, what a loser. "Where’s Rene?"

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content: “Who?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "My maid.”

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content:
“…No clue.”

…

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "She was just with me!"

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content: “Well, then, how do you think you managed to lose her?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I don’t know, that’s why I’m asking you, moron!?" Why do I have to deal with this idiot?

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content: “I don’t know why you’d expect me to be familiar with your own associates.” They scowl at the walls.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Because I’m the main character! I work for Eulogia."

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content: “Eulogia…? What does she have to do with any of this?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "What? She’s like… Umm… She’s like god."

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content:
“…” Arrive doesn’t really know how to respond to that.

They’re startled by one of the blocked doorways suddenly becoming disturbed, bits of rubble shaking slightly.

The wall caves in on itself further. The ceiling collapses. Virtos Dextrum wakes up.

A woman effortlessly shoves aside whatever is needed to make her way towards you. It is obvious upon arrival that this is Rikarasu Endo.

“Where…? Where is she?!” She screams, grabbing you by the collar.

((End session))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Rikarasu continues shaking you roughly.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "D-Don’t touch me!"

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content: "I can do worse than that!" She lets go, calming herself slightly. "Where is Rikarasu Endo? You must have seen her lately, this setting is way too cramped to avoid anyone."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "What? She’s you."

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content:
She blinks rapidly. "...Oh, right. That's going to be annoying. Call me..."

She doesn't come up with whatever she's searching for in time. "...TA." She says the letters T and A sequentially.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I’m not dealing with your garbage again, Rikarasu."

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content:
"That's fine. It really doesn't matter who you think I am. Actually, maybe this is better...? Hard to say." She looks up.

"Irrrelevant..." She points to Arrive. Her eyes land on Virtos Dextrum, just coming to. "Oh, him. Well, I don't think he matters right now."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "But I matter?"

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content: "You're a participant, so nominally, yes. If you really want to matter, you should probably head to where everything is going down. The big boss of this farce of a prelude to my part is getting dealt with as we speak."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "There’s a bossfight!?"

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content: "Yeah, obviously. This is an rpg. It ends with some stupid asshole the party has to take down." She mutters something in Japanese to herself.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Where!?"

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content:
She looks around. 

"...That way." She points in a direction. "Probably."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

It's Hirer's turn. "Ah, Joliene. I've come back from hell, to..." He stares at Katrielle. "Is this supposed to be a fight? I don't really do that, sorry."

Katrielle rolls her eyes. ~~She doesn't have sprites of Kyrie Ushiromiya attached because the joke is too much tedious effort for me right now.~~ "This is a-- we're overthrowing the government, obviously. Is no one paying attention?"

Zita is still silent.

"...To force me to remarry?"

She turns back to the direction of the action. She looks like she has something to say, but doesn't know how to word it.

"What? No. Why would I... look, I lost, big time. Law ain't working out. It's back to being a scoundrel for a bit." Hirer shrugs.

Abruptly noticing the skirmishing of some rebels near him, Hirer hides behind Katrielle. This ends his turn.

Katrielle looks the opposition over, reloading her gun. "...You ready to lay down your life for this, Joliene?"

It hits.

"Heh. I'm the cure. I'm the will of the people. I'm not an old decrepit corpse. I made my own life so I'd *stop* being a rot on society." Catarina coughs.

Hirer Dreng stands there uselessly again. He suddenly doubles over in pain. "Oomf!" He makes a sound akin to this.

"It's her stupid fucking debate gimmick. You can't just not respond to her, Dreng. This was one of her big signature overtures in her political career. She can force people to pay attention to what she's saying to them. Pathetic." Catarina rolls her eyes.

Proso arises victorious. For all her bluster and confidence, Katrielle is now passed out on the ground. Her name is too redundantly similar to someone else here, anyway.

messages.content:
ohhhhg my god no way guys is that a fucking grab oh is that a fucking

In the roleplaying game dungeons and dragons, conflict between two player characters that revolves around grabbing or restraint are handled using the same system of dice rolls, as a ‘grapple contest’. For the one initiating the interaction, their physical strength is tested, whereas for the one put on the defense, it can be either physical strength or dexterity. This is representative of how one can either skillfully weave their way out of an assailant’s grasp, or overpower them and render their attempt irrelevant. Though this asymmetry is a bit strange. Surely dexterity plays a role in being able to successfully operate as an aggressor, too? Regardless.

This is it. A single, solitary, binary check that results in either “grappled” or “not grappled”. There is no room for any other result. In truth, such mechanics being used between player characters isn’t something the system is designed for. It’s a technicality and an edge case. Conflict between humans is not the primary purpose of the set of rules and systems. But isn’t it better this way? Isn’t this real? The only thing to be at all real? What a fucking waste of time everything else has been! I’m really glad we made it here, for these guys to immediately attempt to kill each other.

You know, Bruna doesn’t actually do anything. She doesn’t intervene for some time, because she’s a fucking idiot caught by surprise. It’s just a matter of these two! Wow!!!!

author.name: scipe

author.name: scipe

messages.content: "Because Voreverl is an unbearable and disgusting human being." Theseus says flatly. "And I'm tired."

author.name: onnieee

messages.content: Theseus doesn't deign to respond to that. No one in the world could possibly understand. Ever.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

author.name: scipe

messages.content: "Hm... Yes, I see. You've got quite the good eye, Bruna. Recognizing that I, Voreverl Leocot, am really cool. You may yet be able to rise in the ranks of servitude in my empire of darkness and depravity."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: "Gweh... okay, okay... villain time. I may not be able to decimate both armies, but any soldier who attacks me doesn't stand a chance! We'll get out of this safe! And then... then, from the ashes of a crippled monarchy, my reign of terror will rise!" Voreverl picks up her pace.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: They encounter the dead deceased corpse of Wress Hifele on the ground. A man is staring down at it, unmoving.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: Voreverl almost trips over herself coming to a stop, and looks at this with an expression of horror.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Wress." Theseus says quietly. They are so very used to dead things. They are consciously and physically aware of the consequences of revolution. But Wress's corpse is something new. It's a violent intrusion into a world that was already broken-beyond-measure, the destruction of that fantasy of fixing things. Of coming to some sort of resolution with him, over. Everything. It's that which's most baffling, to Theseus - how little sense it makes, the banality of their final conversation. How banal it *all* becomes in retrospect, with whatever "it" implies remaining unknown to even them. A transactionary dynamic between strangers. No camaraderie to it. The alternative cannot be suffered. Whatever Theseus had thought, does think, becomes suddenly irrelevant, cast into harsh disbelief. How little it had all mattered, in the end.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: Theseus looks to the man. The movement of their head is sluggish and slow, as if someone's cast their body in amber and they are wading through it; they are drowning.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: Voreverl's eyes dart between the body, the man, and Theseus. Her hand shakily extends to her shortsword, clattering it around. She stares angrily at her own hand, and uses her free one to slap herself across the face, before letting out a yell. "You! ...Man! Did you kill my enemy!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
He’s shaken out of his stupor. “…No. But I couldn’t save him. Maybe that’s just as bad.” 
He stares ahead, further forward in the labyrinthian structure of this god-forsaken castle. “He was killed by that bitch. All along, she…” He trails off.

Theseus would theoretically recognize this man as part of the rebel group, though not know his name.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Voreverl lets go of the sword, and casts her gaze away from the corpse. "No... It's *not* just as bad. If you didn't kill him, you're just pointless. Who's 'that bitch'? Who stole my kill? Who do I need to add to my revenge on the world!?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "The queen. Zita Praxis. Or whatever alias she uses. I didn't take her into account. I didn't think she would do anything..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Right." Theseus says coldly. They feel vaguely like they're going to vomit, which really wouldn't.. fit the whole vibe, huh? The violent revenge quest thing they're doing. For Bern, and Furn, and now Wress, and before all of that their *parents*, fuck...

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: "...Damn it! Fucking... damn it!" Voreverl just starts punching a wall "First... my da-... John... now... this asshole... Ugh! Just let me kill someone! They deserve my wrath! This idiot... dragged me into a revolution... he locked me up... he dared to... doubt my evil... why!? Augh!!!" With one final punch, her knuckles completely scraped and bleeding, she just collapses down to the ground, tired and on the verge of tears.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Theseus just stares at her, feeling vaguely sick. What the *fuck* is her problem, like actually? Complaining over not being able to *hurt* enough people? Such an obvious display of weakness as a plea for sympathy. Curled up on the ground as if she needs someone to console her for horrific failure, as if this isn't something that should really get her put down like a sick dog! Wow!

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: Theseus tries to say something to her. "G-" Their voice cracks, embarrassingly. Fuck. Their eyes dart back and forth between John Rebel and Voreverl and Bruna-whatever-the-fuck and Wress's *body*, which is what it is, and that's so much more comprehensible than Furn was, this state of death. Absolute isolation from the living world.

It helps you achieve none of your goals... real change is only effected by being out in the real world. And, here we are."

Viotto can react to this, but not very effectively. His leg is pinned by a piece of rubble as he dodges out of the way. Magnolia is less lucky. Her abdomen is pierced through by a support beam. She is not going to make it. Not this version of her, at least.

"My life has been built around one idea... course correction, you could call it..."
The paper is shifting.
"When we speak into this world... do we expect our outcries to be met... with universal compliance? Or... do we choose people for a quality they alone possess...? If... if..."
...
"If this were my confession..."
...
...

Catarina.

“…No.”

messages.content: "Intuition Overdrive wouldn't do that." She stares at you, a bizarre look in her eyes. "Intuition Overdrive is self-confident, and blazingly stubborn. He acts based on impulse. Every action of his should be in line with the nominal principles of 'intuition'."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "So... so.....your saying that all of what I said...all of that? Was because I did it out of impulse? Not because I actually cared?"

author.name: theotherschilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7ce08f8bae2d1252a0092c317eb39b0d-F721D.png

messages.content: "That's how you show you care, isn't it? Your... love language, so to speak."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Well yeah......that is. I never said I abandoned it."

author.name: theotherschilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7ce08f8bae2d1252a0092c317eb39b0d-F721D.png

messages.content: "...I always found that strange, you know." Lacking anything else to do, Joliene blinks. "Building your identity around everyone's primary method of problem solving."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.name: thebeginnersguide

messages.content: "Yeah... it's why I don't really want it anymore.... it's interesting. I used Intuition as a name as a quirky way to emphasize a character trait.... and spread the way of Intuition or something as way for name to be heard... but the more i think about. If my goal was for everyone else to see who I am and acknowledge it...isn't that just.. wanting to be normal?"

messages.content:
“It’s true.” Zita mutters. “I…”

“Ah, go figure. Hilarious.” 
The Rikarasu-looking-fellow chuckles. 
“Joliene’s one thing, her role here is expected. It’s like a Sativolon sort of thing. But go figure Erica couldn’t even do a single thing right. I thought being attracted to me would maybe allow you to overcome the bias of… I don’t know, having spoken to her once before? Being an incoherent telephone-game caricature of what an online fascist is like? What a joke. I’m sure you want to talk it out endlessly with your cool trick, but unfortunately, this scene isn’t about you.” 

Erica’s turn ends. The Adversary uses her turn to make it her turn. 

“And Intuition! Jeez, it really seemed like there was something there, but I guess you’re exactly as I’d heard about, huh? Maybe if this fight was over with more quickly you could’ve retained a coherent and consistent motivation through the whole thing! Anything else? Catarina, are you ready to have a change of heart and decide violence is never the answer?” The Adversary shakes her head, smirking. “I guess this makes it easier. I was supposed to oppose the participants, anyway. I’ll knock out two birds with one stone!”

I guess that’s Dextrum and Culbasko’s fault for whatever asinine criteria they had in choosing you lot.” TA’s turn ends.

Zita seems to have noticed something in the distance. Her expression undergoes an incomprehensible shift, and she casts a ray of light off into the distance. It kills or otherwise injures a decent amount of random people in its path. With the way cleared, she makes eye contact with a girl one room over, in the direction of the way Intuition (but not Erica) entered the throne room.

“Yoooouuu!” She screams, absurdly loudly. “Th—that’s…” She stares ahead in some incomprehensible mixture of elation and fear.

She addresses the group one final time. “Any last guesses? The big secret, underlying all of this? For the record, I didn’t have this knowledge fed to me by biased insider information. It’s just *obvious* when you’re actually paying attention. …This goes for all of you on Zita’s side too, by the way! I’m about to reveal it anyway, so if anyone has any suspicions they want to bring up to have bragging rights before I topple everything, there’s really no harm in that.” She looks over everyone politely.

“**Many public officials have consistently met Aodh Praxis, and would testify to that effect.**” She shouts at TA.

“People’s word can be bought, can’t it?” TA continues to smirk.

“The type of con you’re purporting is absurd. The funds of this kingdom are not limitless. Someone would break the vow of secrecy. I’ve learned not to trust just anyone in my years adjacent to politics.”

Zita ends her turn. 

Wyrd uses his turn to rush to TA and slash at her, which she dodges.

“Well, that much is true.” TA shrugs.

“I am on the side of the stability and future of the nation.” Wyrd says this.

“No, you aren’t.” TA rolls her eyes. “What a joke. I sincerely hope Voreverl won’t realize she’s a bad guy and then decide to give up on fighting too because of that. …Oh, yeah, I guess I have to say this next part, since I’m pretty sure only MBMJ saw the most damning evidence related to this…” TA clears her throat. “So, disguise magic exists. It could’ve been someone else purporting to be Aodh. Like, say, Virtos. Or any arbitrary collaborator. Can you name a single instance of Aodh supposedly meeting with someone while outdoors, or in another situation where disguising would fail?” TA steps back defensively, away from Wyrd. But only as a symbolic gesture, I guess, because it’s still Erica’s initiative.

messages.content:
“Okay, I never mentioned that, but whatever.”

Wyrd makes it his turn. He attacks Catarina.

Zita speaks. “It is entirely reasonable for professional contexts to be indoors. **Those close to Aodh — his family and immediate associates within this building — would testify to seeing him in, for instance, the garden, countless times.**”

“Are you serious? That’s your counter? Is this a joke?” TA puts a hand to her hip.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
“…” Zita is silent.

“They would obviously lie for the sake of someone close to them.” TA points out.

“Someone you claim to already be dead?!” Zita.

“No, not Aodh.” TA points at Zita. “You, obviously.”

Zita grips her polearm. She lets out a violent sob that doesn’t manifest into words, before speaking again. 
“Do you see any of them here? I am a failure as a mother and a person. **Aodh’s brother or personal associates would not lie out of any allegiance to me.**” She grits her teeth.
“**Eulogia Praxis would not lie out of love for me! Detlef Praxis would not lie out of love for me! Catarina Praxis would not lie out of love for me!!!**” 

Wyrd slashes at Catarina with each remark. Zita’s daughter collapses to the ground, unconscious, precariously close to death.

((Ending the session here.))

messages.content:
“It should be Detlef, right?” TA asks no one in particular, because no one gives a shit. “The monarchy chooses the firstborn male. That’s what makes Catarina spiteful, what reflects the general misogyny of Arctican culture. So it’s him. …But… that feels off. He seems so… unimportant. None of you ever talk about him. Like, at all. He was sent onto Earth as an afterthought and got stuck there. And no one bothered retrieving him for quite a while.”

“We understand, you hold no respect for the government or those connected to it.” Proso rolls his eyes. “This doesn’t matter in the slightest.”

“…I don’t think it’s actually him.” TA muses.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Then who?" Joliene questions this from the floor.

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
“I understand now. It must be someone else already dead. That’s the problem — because the rules of succession had a massive hole, you were left with an inability to legitimately maintain your family’s power. …Everything still seems like overkill if we’re just basing it on that, but I imagine there’s some magical nonsense here too. That you’re bound by duty or some vow to follow the way the monarchy operates to the letter, and you draw strength from that. Or something. It doesn’t particularly matter how the nuances of the motive operate.” TA shrugs.

The wall of force having faded by now, a man enters, guarded by a handful of people. Many of the soldiers, both on the rebel and government side, stop their fighting and back off uncertainly upon his arrival.

“…My name is Virtos Dextrum.” Virtos Dextrum says this, his voice echoing through the location.

messages.content:
“I am the advisor to the throne. And this is, perhaps, the most vital piece of advice I will ever give it.”

He sighs, and lowers his voice, addressing one person rather than the entire room. “…Stand down, Zita. You’ve done your best, but the jig is up. The current status quo holds zero legal legitimacy. …Well done, Rikarasu.”

“There’s nothing to congratulate. It was an entirely non-functional mystery. I’m simply built differently than lesser minds.” TA sneers.

messages.content:
“In your stead, I’ve negotiated with the rebel forces Arrive let in, while you’ve stuck out here fighting some endless unwinnable battle. A peaceful transition of power is possible. A compromise. Enough people have died already.” Virtos shakes his head solemnly.

“…Shut your mouth, you whore.” Zita hisses. “Nothing is settled! No one is dead! It’s all lies.”

Proso looks between her and Virtos, uncertain.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

"This isn't right. There's something everyone is failing to consider here."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "That, in spite of whatever technicalities and needlessly elaborate lies you claim exist, Zita is still suited for her position on her throne. Like it or not, she's a born leader; if she managed to keep Arctica a functioning nation with the actual monarch dead, overseeing every responsibility as capably as she did, all while keeping the truth of Aodh's death a perfect secret, then that's actually *more* impressive than her responsibilities as Queen normally. We can't be so quick to foist her from her position, should these claims be true; it's illogical at best and horribly disrespectful at worst."

This is it. This is the person that’s at this dead end. We’re all very proud of you, Theseus. So much so that we’re even dignifying that name, instead of using Horatius, or Lyra. You’ve escaped from the devious machinations of kings and queens and gods. You’ve found true freedom, and it’s presenting you with a beautiful choice, to talk to an ancillary time-displaced elf racist for the rest of time or jump off a tower and off yourself. We’re all very impressed by your refusal of the call. This is all quite powerful. Bravo.
