users.name: metalcicada
users.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\07f54889ceff548977463144d973ac63-E62A9.png

messages.content: She chuckles. “Ahhh… people here really are incompetent. It’s cute. I grow tired of all this, however. The squabbling of this era provides little of relevance to my life.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Theseus continues to look at her like she's mentally ill. Which, to be fair, she probably is. "Why are you here?"

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: Surely this question will make everything clear. Surely all will be revealed. Surely, at some point, the pieces will come together, a conflagration of immediate and impressed meaning. There has to be a meaning or purpose for them being here. The alternative is some grand existential terror Theseus is not quite ready to grapple with.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content:
“I wound up here after my ship crashed. For some time, I had trouble leaving, but at this point, I simply do not know where else to go.”

She stared off at the horizon. “I saw someone important to me earlier. My parent. I think they are avoiding me. Did I do something wrong? I know there are people who hate me out of spite and jealousy. But I have worked hard to make those I am indebted to proud.” She frowns, and turns to you. “What is your name, commoner?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: My name, Theseus thinks. My name. Everyone wants my name. Everyone wants whatever piece of me they can get, a symbol of ownership, of.. something. It means something. Giving out my name means something.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: "Theseus."

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: “I see. It is nice to meet you, Theseus. My name is Nerissa Titinius. …I did think even the lower classes in this era had surnames, though. Have you forsaken your kin?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Theseus lets their mouth curl up into a slight smile. There are no consequences to this, are there? No amount of vulnerability here will ever be used against them. They're off on an island away from all signs of life. This is just what's left over.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: "Mm. Something like that. Or.. more accurate to say they've forsaken me."

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: It's not entirely a lie. It doesn't feel like one to say.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: “I see. I’m sorry, then. My mother and father are also dead. So I understand your pain completely and without any issue.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I'm sorry for your loss." Theseus says. They stare off in the same direction she's staring off. Is.. anything there?

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content:
The capital. Some of the chaos engulfing it has died down. Many buildings are in ruins.

The sky is still the sky.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Theseus takes a moment to just look at it. The chalky smear of a still-smoking sky. This, unsuprisingly, isn't the sort of thing you just come back from. It's a total and complete upheaval of the natural order of things, the heuristics and structures and frameworks dedicating life-as-is. Theseus just doesn't know what the future looks like, after this. They had an idea, but like so many other things, that idea is dead now. It is too late; this body of earth is changed.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: Theseus turns around. They don't want to look anymore.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: “…Point three. On my future.” She says out loud, an entirely incoherent set of words.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Bwuh?" Theseus says, intelligently.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content:
“I hope that with that, I have earned the privilege of some selfishness. In the same region I store this tome away, my most powerful yet vexing creation is also sealed away. I have tried and failed to maintain and properly look after it. I can only believe that the person who finds this will be a suitable caretaker. I am sorry, Nerissa. I hope, for your sake and for mine, you live a life such that you never think of me as your father.” She recites all this quickly and emotionlessly, like someone hyperfixated on some work of fiction enough to know its script by heart. Or like some other simile that isn’t absolute ass.

“Theseus, do you think people can just be unlucky? If you are abandoned and forsaken repeatedly, it doesn’t necessarily *have* to be the fault of you, the one common element, right?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Theseus thinks for a minute. "...No." They say, eventually. It's so hollow. It doesn't mean anything. They could lie to comfort her and no one would ever know.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: But. But.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: "It has to be someone's fault, in the end."

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: “I suppose.” She nods. “It’s everyone else’s then, I think. A man tried to kill me recently! *Me!* I am, eternally, a victim.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Sure." Theseus says. "You can believe that, if you want. It may even by true for you." They cough indelicately. "I'm not in a position to say."

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: “Alright.” She nods rapidly and repeatedly. “You’re a credit to your people, young man. Thank you for this talk, Theseus.” She smiles warmly.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Conversation success.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content: "You're welcome." They say. Although they don't know if they've earned it.

author.name: onnieee
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\af114b26c161ebe1376c2e8061cbd7d4-EDAEE.png

messages.content:
With friends like these.

((end chapter))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

guild.name: TAP
guild.iconUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\421e4b7d67024c8299c3aca3da0cc405-61B0F.png

messages.content:
Solnit leads MBMJ to a door, presumably the VIRTOS DEXTRUM ROOM. “Well… we didn’t encounter it on the way here, but… be prepared for anything.”
He slowly makes to open it.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **MBMJ gives a big thumbs up.**

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
Solnit opens the door. No one is immediately visible in what looks like a pretty standard bureaucrat’s office.
“Hm.” He enters.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **MBMJ enters as well.** "Heh, the unassuming office of an unassuming gentleman... what a classic find!"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
It has a desk, a variety of books, some cabinets, an MBMJ mask for some odd reason, and a single door in the back.

Solnit rummages through the cabinets for a moment.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **MBMJ tiptoes to the door in the back like he's Dennis the Menace.**

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: “That would be the next step, yes…” Solnit mumbles. “Was I mistaken…? Is the abberance still inert within there?” He leaves the cabinets and trails behind you.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **MBMJ opens the door and looks inside.**

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
It’s empty. Mostly. It contains a circular platform floating in a starry void. A small point of light is hovering above the center.

“Dammit. Did she… did it… did I fail? Hang on, um…” Solnit brushes past you.

((End session here sowwy))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
After some examination of this room, Solnit sighs heavily. 

"Man... what are we doing...?"

(( @Mr. Big Man III ))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

mentions.name: swigglemcdiggle
mentions.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: "The two of us? RIght now? Right now the two of us are rhizomal truth-seekers, bound entropically to delve ever deeper into Mamma Mana's machinations. Our natures have guided us here, at the precipice of this fractured wisdom. And now you ask of me, is it worth it to continue on? Buddy, no matter how tiny and fleeting the potential metaphorical prize, it is still worth taking, for in heaven's oiled up arena, if you throw in the towel, all that's left to wear are the pasties of What Already Is."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: “I don’t know what that means, sorry. I’ve spent a long time avoiding throwing in the towel, no matter how many people demanded that of me. How many cowards who would rather I just resign myself to irrelevance, quit on my endeavors to achieve the ideal outcome… I know that part, at least. But at some point, it becomes a question of whether you’re no wiser than an obsessed gambler or raving lunatic…” Solnit stares at the light.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **MBMJ attempts to jump up and touch the light.**

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: Solnit holds an arm out to stop him, though mainly as a gesture indicating he shouldn’t. He’s too weak right now to muster up physical resistance. “…Probably not a good idea.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...And what is?"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: “I don’t… it’s just that that’s… Earth. …In essence. The effects of direct physical contact here are inconsistent.” He sci-fi handwaves. “Unless you want to try your luck for some way out of this mess, which I wouldn’t blame you for.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "So Earth physically exists, in... Arctica?"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: “Kind of…? It’s a question that brings up what we mean by ‘physical’. When you entered Eulogia’s dream, was that physically in Arctica?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Well, no, but none of what I was doing in her dreams was manifested in Arctica. But if that's Earth..."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: “Iiiit’s, difficult to summarize the topological layout in one word… It’s almost like one of those Elvithan nesting dolls… or perhaps a finger trap… the point is, Earth is our creation. Or Ambilo’s, to be precise. Dextrum’s forefather. Though its original purpose has been far surpassed in complexity…”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Oh. Okay, cool."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: "Did they create us as well?"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: He laughs. “You put on quite an act of bluster, but you’re actually rather perceptive, aren’t you? In some regards, that question is the core of everything you’ve found yourself caught up in. …It depends on who you mean by they, and it also depends on who you ask.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "And so to what end do I inspect this orb in front of my current visage? Is it the reflector or originator of divine truth? Is it only a thermometer in the machinations of king and queencraft or is it thatself a wholly consequential vessel, ripe with significance and complete causality? What a quandary indeed!"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: “Yes, exactly.” He nods.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "...So what are you in for?"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
“I thought I’d fight for my ideals from inside the system. This was supposed to be the day everything was building towards, but… some stupid, bad luck, just happenstance, that *he* would…” Solnit curses under his breath. Suddenly, he turns, startled, to the door. You can see some unusual motion on his back, underneath his cloak. 

A second later, a man enters, wielding a katana and wearing a fedora. He looks around disinterested.
“Who are you lot, then?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "HI, I'm Mr. Big Man Jr. I'm a hero, and a wrestler. I always fight on the side of justice."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
“Oh, I think I’ve heard of you, yeah.” Fedora man nods.

“You’re the intruder here—!” Solnit coughs.

“Name’s Isador.” He extends his hand out to MBMJ.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: **MBMJ extends his hand to shake.**

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
A handshake is performed. Solnit watches this silently.

“…This place looks different from when I was last here.” Isador mutters.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Oh wow. More fellow witnessers of one of the world's most profound vistas..."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: “I dunno if I’d call it that.” Isador. “It’s more just… nostalgia, than any actual admiration for this location’s craftsmanship or whatever. Kinda gaudy, if you ask me.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Ah, sorry to interject my unlearned opinion. This is indeed very serious business."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
“Ah, it’s fine. Pretty sure barely anybody has the full picture of what’s going on here. Maybe fuckin’ Virtos Dextrum…”

“Who are you? How do you know about this place?” Solnit demands threateningly, despite the lack of any clear means to carry out a threat.

“You don’t know me? …Well, I guess I don’t really know who you are either…” Isador murmurs.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Our unfamiliarity does not spread us, like raindrops, but instead forces us to rely on each other like the bunched banana!

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: "We are all friends here."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: “That’s nice, man.” Isador stares at the point of light. “What’s that?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Earth."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
Solnit looks angrily at him but doesn’t say anything. 

“Ah, alright. That makes sense. Vaguely. You know, I’m actually from Earth. So that’s most of the explanation for why I’ve been here.” Isador.

“What? No, that explains nothing.” Solnit is baffled.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Narratively, perhaps."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content: “Narrative, huh? Haha. Y’know, I used to love fantasy stories. …I guess that’s kind of nonsense to you two, but like, the way things work around here… it’s basically the realm of dreams and made up bullshit where I come from.” Isador.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Huh. I suppose that introduces some asymmetry between us. We do not as of yet fictionalize of your world, to my knowledge."

author.name: swigglemcdiggle

messages.content:
“Crazy. I guess there’s not much to write about there.”

“Some speculative fiction has happened to be slightly similar to what Earth is like.” Solnit notes. “But on the whole, no. …Earth itself is analogous to a story. I think it was originally created to test out alternative forms of governance.”

“You would.” Solnit mutters.

“Huh?” Bruna stares at him.

“…” Solnit looks away.

“…The queen recognized me. I don’t understand. I’ve never met her, I don’t think? She’s terrifying, though.” Bruna puts a hand on her shoulder.

messages.content:
“We’re not. …I don’t… think?” Bruna holds her head. “I know her. Maybe. It feels like… I can’t feel the way I do about her, logically. And that kind of scares me.” She crouches down in front of Solnit. “I never pushed Dextrum on the issue of where I came from, since I honestly didn’t care. But it feels like it’s starting to become relevant. You must know, right? He tells you everything. Who… am I? Did you really just find me somewhere…?”

Solnit clears his throat. “A…”
…He continues to silently sulk.

messages.content: "Imagine betting on a sheet of a million matches between two million wrestlers in a truly fair sportlike competition, over and over and over. Every individual match is a reflection of what could've happened from the word go of the beginning, when the bichromatic striped messenger of futility rings the bell. Technically, anything could happen, as I used to say to my good old Berry Boy. But eventually, you might believe that you have learned enough to make a bet at the betting boy in your dreams. And when you have done that is when you have defined entropy."

“…What?” She stares at him. “Who? Huh??”

author.name: scipe

messages.content:
“In theory, at least.” Solnit nods.

“Who the fuck is Bruce Praxis?!” Bruna asks, agitated.

“…The king was always interested in pushing the boundaries of magic. And past a certain point, his wife seemed to gain a fixation on resurrection.” Solnit rolls his eyes. “Catarina’s twin died in the womb. But Zita thought she could fix that. Years later… ‘Bruce Praxis’ showed up. I don’t know from where. I don’t even know where exactly Virtos found you, frankly. But you’re apparently one and the same as the man who was, for a time and in secret, the presumptive future ruler of this country.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Queeeeeeens oh my god!!!!!!!"

author.name: swigglemcdiggle
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\007126dd79b46a811fb1464305d708ed-F78E4.png

messages.content:
“…That doesn’t feel right. I mean, I guess I wouldn’t know, but… surely this would’ve come up? I’ve lived a normal life as a simple humble wrestling publicist for years now.”

“There’s not many people who would recognize you. And Virtos always made sure you never crossed paths with them. That’s why you lived all the way out in another corner of the kingdom.”

“Huh.” Bruna sits down. “That still seems wrong. Like, a fake red herring answer to whatever the mystery that is my life is.”

“Well, he always thought you were only ever going to be who you wanted to be.” Solnit rolls his eyes. “Awfully sentimental for a monster.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

“The law can’t catch me. Heh.” He smirks.

messages.content:
Zita steps back.
“You’re all… even you, Joliene? You’re buying this… nonsense?”

“Zita, please.” Virtos begs. “I understand your grief. I do, really. But it isn’t your fault, and it doesn’t have to define you or our world.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I'm not. I was speaking hypothetically. The only thing you have to worry about is everybody being too caught up in their own mistaken assumptions to listen to reason."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
“Well… okay, I’m… Dextrum… you traitor…!”

“I am no traitor.” Virtos Dextrum shakes his head. “You are closer to that, but I don’t wish to accuse you of any ill intent. Again: nothing that has happened is your fault.” Virtos lies. Everything’s her fucking fault, obviously.

“Shut up! Obviously things that *didn’t happen* are not my fault! Aodh never died! And Bruce is alive, he was just here a moment ago!” She gestures in the direction the wall of force used to exist.

“No. He wasn’t. You’re mistaken.” Virtos shakes his head.

“Bruce was dead for a time, so… at the very least, that end of the claims is less deluded. But he returned! The magic worked! I atoned!!!” She screams.

“There is no scientific backing to the idea that anything about your emotional state or motives could have caused a miscarriage. Why are you being so irrational about this? Despite the front you present, you’re an exceptionally intelligent woman, Zita. Think this through further, and you’ll understand it’s your best option.” Virtos calmly explains.

Zita glares daggers at him. “…This is Earth’s fault, isn’t it? That’s what corrupted you. It corrupted all of my children one by one. Made my sons forget who they were, my daughters forget who they should be. Your idiotic pet project.”

Dextrum sighs.

messages.content: Unable to use a sneak attack, Voreverl decides the best course of action is to make use of her warlock training. She casts four beams of eldritch blast at Zita.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
The first misses, but as she draws closer, Voreverl is able to hit Zita consistently with the remaining three.

Zita topples over onto the ground, her momentum carrying her tumbling forward to be crumpled in a heap right in front of Voreverl.

Joliene and Zita are disabled. The forces of the monarchy are outnumbered and uncertain. Combat proper ends, for the moment.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: She attempts to crawl back into her wheelchair, initiative being over.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: This will take some time.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
Voreverl stares down in disgust. The villain kills the hero. Voreverl grabs her shortsword with both hands. The villain kills the villain. Voreverl steadies her grip. The villain disposes of the heap of trash. Voreverl positions her sword over Zita's neck. Voreverl Leocot. Voreverl Leocot. Voreverl Leocot.

I kill her. I'm sorry I took so long, dad.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Wait, no--!" Virtos extends a hand, but he's nowhere close. He can't stop this. No one can.

Zita freezes, and then shoves Voreverl back. She rips the sword out of herself, tossing it. She screams in agony. Blood pours chaotically through the midsection of her wyrd-shaped bindings like water through a breached dam.
She stares at Voreverl. She stops screaming. A faint smile comes to her face. "...It really should've been Lyra."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.name: scipe

messages.content: Zita's bleeding slows. Her eyes grow clouded. Her knees buckle and lose their strength.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
...She takes another step forward.

Zita stares, confused, at her own movement. Perhaps her spirit is unwilling to die quite yet.

Her bindings shift. They tighten. A thread maneuvers itself past her arms and around her neck.

Zita gasps for air. Zita can't breathe.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content:
Zita's head topples over. It seems whatever she used to keep her hair tied up came off, from the chaos of battle or something. Her face is no longer visible. Wyrd takes a step forward.

"...Voreverl. You should probably leave." Virtos Dextrum speaks in a voice entirely unfamiliar to anyone present. He's normally too stupid to feel fear.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: This is good. Joliene had a feeling things were going to work themselves out. Yes.

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content: "I was just waiting for the show to end." Voreverl gives a lazed wave to everyone present. "Have fun working out politics or whatever. Not my problem anymore." She makes a break for whatever looks like the exit.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Wyrd swings his arm at Voreverl. He misses. He goes further. Zita's arm dislocates. Wyrd successfully grabs Voreverl. Wyrd throws Voreverl onto the ground face first. Voreverl breaks her nose.

The Adversary arrives. "Unbelievable. Why would this happen?"

"That outfit. It..." Virtos starts saying something.

"I don't actually care. It's a problem to be dealt with. Zita can't be alive in any sense of the word." The Adversary sighs.

The building shakes.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Voreverl rolls over and feels her nose. "Ow... Whatever, if Zita's dead, I did what I needed to. I can die here for all I care."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "I think... it was a mistake. To underestimate the Crown."

author.name: thebeginnersguide
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\96bfd6970100265a0c5139863721722f-0A978.png

messages.content:
The Crown. That's one way to put it. It lives on. It used Zita as long as it could. And it still does, through the fragment of it she wove into her alternate persona, mimicking her dead husband in a way that makes no sense at all and is in fact entirely unrelated to the way she actually mimicked her husband by performing his administrative duties. It had an ideological link, though. Zita was loyal to the very end, but it's unclear what the hell it is she was loyal *to*.

Maybe there's something poetic, then, about this shambling, unstoppable lifeless body. Is that why magic works the way it does? For whatever facilitates the best descriptive metaphor?

Wyrd uses his weapon and cuts clean through a rebel who tries to approach him. A royal guard near that rebel meets the same fate. The threads continue to writhe and slither and break various parts of Zita's body.

"Seriously, though. Where the hell *did* Rikarasu go?" The Adversary mutters. If anyone is still looking at her, they'd see her hands start to glow black as she runs to Wyrd.

((End chapter.))

messages.content: "I don't quite know, but this is Catarina's whole shtick. Recording and replaying events for propaganda purposes. Remember that whole gameshow? It seems she wanted to do the same for her amazing revolution. But now I have it. I can do whatever I want to the footage, splice it to remove my untimely defeat. I'll be a *hero*, Intuition. I'll suck up to these idiot idealists and take what's mine. Information is power! That's what I've learned in all my years."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7ce08f8bae2d1252a0092c317eb39b0d-F721D.png

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Him?!!! Him?!!! That enabler? He constantly spat nonsense about "protecting women". "protecting" Catarina Praxis. And look where I am now. I'm dead. I didn't do shit."

author.name: theotherschilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7ce08f8bae2d1252a0092c317eb39b0d-F721D.png

messages.content:
"You aren't dead! Stop saying nonsense! But you could be! I..."
Katrielle Groverfield starts crying.
"I *hate* you... and that's why I did all this..."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "I..... I.... I..... I....." My face gets red. "You have this power! YOU HAVE THIS ALL! Use it or I'll snatch it from you."

author.name: theotherschilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7ce08f8bae2d1252a0092c317eb39b0d-F721D.png

messages.content: "What are you talking about?! I'm *going* to use it! I... just you wait!" She takes a step back.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: *What? What? What? What? Do I do?*

author.name: theotherschilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7ce08f8bae2d1252a0092c317eb39b0d-F721D.png

messages.content: I try to step closer. "That magic you have is mine! I knew it. I knew you were a coward."

author.name: theotherschilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7ce08f8bae2d1252a0092c317eb39b0d-F721D.png

attachments.url: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\confident-264B6.png

messages.content: "You've explained all your motives to me. And now.... I have all the evidence for you to indict of you numerous crimes, really."

author.name: theotherschilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7ce08f8bae2d1252a0092c317eb39b0d-F721D.png

messages.content: "No one will believe you. You're a lunatic. Boy who cried wolf. You've dug your own grave. Unless you want to man up and try to kill me before I manage this coup? I doubt it. You wouldn't."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "Intuition is when you stop thinking. and you start doing. You yourself should have thought about this before you babbled on about all this." I pull my gun.

author.name: theotherschilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7ce08f8bae2d1252a0092c317eb39b0d-F721D.png

messages.content:
Intuition doesn't have a gun.

"I took that. ...You were out of bullets anyway, though." She reaches into her other pocket and tosses it to you. "Worthless."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "And that was your fatal mistake. You know that a blank can still kill someone, right? Heated gasses in the barrel can be shot with enough force to damage something."

author.name: theotherschilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7ce08f8bae2d1252a0092c317eb39b0d-F721D.png

messages.content:
"You don't *have* any blanks. Incompetent. I really did fail to raise you, huh? I..." She trails off. Katrielle lifts a hand to her face. She realizes only now that she's crying. Her eyes widen in fear.

"Fuck." Katrielle runs.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: I let her run off, and I unload the gun.

author.name: theotherschilalyi
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7ce08f8bae2d1252a0092c317eb39b0d-F721D.png

messages.content: The gun is already unloaded. Seriously, what is your goal here.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: Or like. There's nothing in the gun. There aren't bullets in the gun. There aren't blanks in the gun. The place where ammunition is stored in a gun does not have anything in it for this gun. Because you don't have any.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\76f49d11f9160bac20c987b4dbc5c23a-F34F2.png

messages.content: "There was a difference between no ammo and blanks?"

embeds.title: Blank (cartridge)
embeds.description: A blank is a firearm cartridge that, when fired, does not shoot a projectile like a bullet or pellet, but generates a muzzle flash and an explosive sound (muzzle report) like a normal gunshot would. Firearms may need to be modified to allow a blank to cycle the action, and the shooter experiences less recoil with a blank than with a live round. ...
